[{"id":"/sicpjs/2.3.1","tag":"TITLE","body":"2.3.1  \n    \n      \n      Strings"},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p1","child":[{"body":"\n\tSo far, we have used strings in order to display messages,\n\tusing the functions ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"display"},{"body":" and\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"error"},{"body":" (as for example in \n\texercise ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"1.22","href":"/sicpjs/1.2.6#ex-1.22"},{"body":"). \n        We can form compound data using strings and have\n\tlinked lists such as\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":true,"eval":false,"body":"\nllist(\"a\", \"b\", \"c\", \"d\")\nllist(23, 45, 17)\nllist(llist(\"Jakob\", 27), llist(\"Lova\", 9), llist(\"Luisa\", 24))\n          "},{"body":"\n        In order to distinguish strings from names, we surround them\n\t\n\twith double quotation marks. For example, the Python expression\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"z"},{"body":" denotes the value of the\n\tname ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"z"},{"body":", whereas the Python\n\texpression ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"\"z\""},{"body":" denotes a string\n\tthat consists of a single character, namely the last letter in the\n\tEnglish alphabet in lower case. \n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p2","child":[{"body":"\n        Via quotation marks, we can distinguish between strings and names:\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":1,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsEMQC8I2ARoUkA","body":"a = 1\nb = 2 "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":2,"eval":true,"prependLength":4,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsEMQC8I2ARoUjgA4BOAlgHYAuAFADau0DOLuANCCQCUgoA","body":"print(llist(a, b)) ","output":"[1, [2, None]]"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":3,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsAcBOAlgHYAuAFADaWEDOFARAIYMA0IDARgwJQ9A","body":"print(llist(\"a\", \"b\")) ","output":"[\"a\", [\"b\", None]]"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":4,"eval":true,"prependLength":4,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsEMQC8I2ARoUjgA4BOAlgHYAuAFADau0DOLARLjwBoQJAJQigA","body":"print(llist(\"a\", b)) ","output":"[\"a\", [2, None]]"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p3","child":[{"body":"\n\tIn section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"1.1.6","href":"/sicpjs/1.1.6"},{"body":", we introduced\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":" and\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"!="},{"body":"\n\tas  primitive predicates on numbers.\n        \n\tFrom now\n\ton, we shall allow two\n\tstrings as operands of\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":" and\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"!="},{"body":". The predicate\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":" \t\n\treturns True if and only\n\tif the two strings are the same, and \n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"!="},{"body":"\n\treturns True if and only\n\tif the two strings are not the same.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-1","body":"1","href":"/sicpjs/2.3.1#footnote-1"},{"body":"\n\tUsing ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":", we can implement\n\ta useful function called ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"member"},{"body":".\n\tThis takes two arguments: a string and a linked list of strings or\n\ta number and a linked list of numbers.\n\tIf the first argument is\n\tnot contained in the linked list (i.e., is not\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":" to any item in the linked list), \n        then ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"member"},{"body":" returns\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"None"},{"body":".  Otherwise, it returns the\n\tsublist of the linked list beginning with the first occurrence of the\n\tstring or number:\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":5,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBMCmAZiALb4kBG+ATgBQCWALuQDQgAeAlAFxYj8hq+RgFdqAOxC0AcgHtx+EPWL0AzgH1x8-LS58BBg-gA2qxeyUrmJEAF5bIABb4Ahrl2d9hwybOlyVHRMrCCMLvTGHpyeWAAO1PTijLRklDS0AEQusbHG+BlsxsZqyRmxrtQFIBkULuJ1LlVl1CIKGdGcQA","body":"def member(item, x):\n    return (None if is_none(x)\n            else x if item == head(x)\n            else member(item, tail(x))) "},{"body":"\n        For example, the value of\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":6,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBMCmAZiALb4kBG+ATgBQCWALuQDQgAeAlAFxYj8hq+RgFdqAOxC0AcgHtx+EPWL0AzgH1x8-LS58BBg-gA2qxeyUrmJEAF5bIABb4Ahrl2d9hwybOlyVHRMrCCMLvTGHpyeWAAO1PTijLRklDS0AEQusbHG+BlsxsZqyRmxrtQFIBkULuJ1LlVl1CIKGdGcQA","body":"print(member(\"apple\", llist(\"pear\", \"banana\", \"prune\"))) "},{"body":"\n        is ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"None"},{"body":", whereas the value of\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":7,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBMCmAZiALb4kBG+ATgBQCWALuQDQgAeAlAFxYj8hq+RgFdqAOxC0AcgHtx+EPWL0AzgH1x8-LS58BBg-gA2qxeyUrmJEAF5bIABb4Ahrl2d9hwybOlyVHRMrCCMLvTGHpyeWAAO1PTijLRklDS0AEQusbHG+BlsxsZqyRnsBSAZcBVZOXk1sa7UGdGcQA","body":"print(member(\"apple\", llist(\"x\", \"y\", \"apple\", \"pear\"))) "},{"body":"\n        is ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"llist(\"apple\", \"pear\")"},{"body":".\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.53","id":"#ex-2.53","child":[{"body":"\n        What is the result of evaluating each of the\n        following expressions, in box notation and linked-list notation?\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":8,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBtcCWAzgC4AUARAIYUA0IFARnQwMYUCUQA","body":"llist(\"a\", \"b\", \"c\") "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":9,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBtcCWAzgC4AU+x5ARAOYCmA9gE4PUCU7QA","body":"llist(llist(\"george\")) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":10,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBcCGAlgDYAUxxhAzruZTaQEQAeGjANCC4owJScVqtRnDacRPXlKA","body":"tail(llist(llist(\"x1\", \"x2\"), llist(\"y1\", \"y2\"))) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":11,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBcCGAlgDYAUAFgKb4AmpxxhAzrvYy6QEQAeGnANCB6JOASkENmrTnD6CZI0UtFA","body":"tail(head(llist(llist(\"x1\", \"x2\"), llist(\"y1\", \"y2\")))) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":12,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBMCmAZiALb4kBG+ATgBQCWALuQDQgAeAlAFxYj8hq+RgFdqAOxC0AcgHtx+EPWL0AzgH1x8-LS58BBg-gA2qxeyUrmJEAF5bIABb4Ahrl2d9hwybOlyVHRMrCCMLvTGHpyeWGSUNLQAREK4iWzGxmqMSRTGIvhpIImqjrL4qoWJcCbGsgDulaqyAMYA1hXRQA","body":"member(\"red\", llist(\"blue\", \"shoes\", \"yellow\", \"socks\")) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":13,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBMCmAZiALb4kBG+ATgBQCWALuQDQgAeAlAFxYj8hq+RgFdqAOxC0AcgHtx+EPWL0AzgH1x8-LS58BBg-gA2qxeyUrmJEAF5bIABb4Ahrl2d9hwybOlyVHRMrCCMLvTGHpyeWGSUNLQAREK4iWzGxmqMSSlpIImqjrL4qnmJFMYi+GWqsgDGANal0UA","body":"member(\"red\", llist(\"red\", \"shoes\", \"blue\", \"socks\")) "}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":14,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsAcBOAlgHYAuAFADaWEDOFARAIYMA0IDARmxwMYMBKAVlABtZj3Hd24-uwByAe2IBTALoagA","body":"print([\"a\", [\"b\", [\"c\", None]]]) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":15,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsAcBOAlgHYAuAFADaWEDOF1dFARAOYCmA9vh8wJQCsoANrC2XHu2YAaEADlOxdgF1ZCpcqA","body":"print([[\"george\", None], None]) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":16,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsAcBOAlgHYAuAFKQIaEA25tthAzhYyxQEQAeGnANCB6JOASkHtW5TnD6CZI0UtFZQAbTUy5ITXBGCAcgHtiAUwC65wyYtA","body":"print([[\"y1\", [\"y2\", None]], None]) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":17,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsAcBOAlgHYAuAFKQIaEA25AFgKZUAm5tthAzhZzxQBEADwyCANCBGJBASkn9e5QXDGSVM2Vq1ZQAbWkSQAOQD2xJgF0gA","body":"print([\"x2\", None]) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":18,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBMCmAZiALb4kBG+ATgBQCWALuQDQgAeAlAFxYj8hq+RgFdqAOxC0AcgHtx+EPWL0AzgH1x8-LS58BBg-gA2qxeyUrmJEAF5bIABb4Ahrl2d9hwybOlyVHRMrCCMLvTGHpyeWAAO1PTijLRklDS0AERCuBlsxsZqyfmFmdm5IBmqjrL4qhmceQWqyRkUxiL45ZWyAMYA1nXR0VigcgpAA","body":"print(None) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":19,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsBMCmAZiALb4kBG+ATgBQCWALuQDQgAeAlAFxYj8hq+RgFdqAOxC0AcgHtx+EPWL0AzgH1x8-LS58BBg-gA2qxeyUrmJEAF5bIABb4Ahrl2d9hwybOlyVHRMrCCMLvTGHpyeWAAO1PTijLRklDS0AESqjrL4qhlsxsZqyRlCuAUgWTl5lRkUxiL4daqyAMYA1vnRnqAA2tW5+WwDDU2VA62dwyByCgC6i0A","body":"print([\"red\", [\"shoes\", [\"blue\", [\"socks\", None]]]]) "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.54","id":"#ex-2.54","child":[{"body":"\n\tTwo linked lists are said to be\n\t ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":"\n\tif they contain equal elements arranged in the same order.  For example,\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":20,"eval":true,"prependLength":3,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgugGYCuAdgMYAuAlgPZEgCmAjgQIYA2IZVIARnSAO4AnCmTJ1a3BAGcyBACbiyOAA7CiZABSMWrDa1YUZGgERkAFoeMAaEMcs3jza7YNEA1nTnPjBmcYCUVlggIaH6hpqmFlLe9rZODq4eXokRAf7+QA","body":"print(equal(llist(\"this\", \"is\", \"a\", \"linked\", \"list\"),\n      llist(\"this\", \"is\", \"a\", \"linked\", \"list\"))) "},{"body":"\n\tis True, but\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":21,"eval":true,"prependLength":3,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgugGYCuAdgMYAuAlgPZEgCmAjgQIYA2IZVIARnSAO4AnCmTJ1a3BAGcyBACbiyOAA7CiZABSMWrDa1YUZGgERkAFoeMAaEMcs3jza7YNEA1nTnPjBmcYCUVlggIaH6hpqmFlLO4UZ2MQ5OgS4U7p7evmQB-gCQoSD+QA","body":"print(equal(llist(\"this\", \"is\", \"a\", \"linked\", \"list\"),\n      llist(\"this\", llist(\"is\", \"a\"), \"linked\", \"list\"))\t    ) "},{"body":"\n\tis False.  To be more precise, we can define\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":" recursively in terms of the\n\tbasic ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":" equality of numbers and\n\tstrings by\n\tsaying that ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"a"},{"body":" and\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"b"},{"body":" are\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":" if they are both strings or\n\tboth numbers and they are\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":", or if they are both pairs such\n\tthat ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"head(a)"},{"body":" is\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":" to\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"head(b)"},{"body":" and \n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"tail(a)"},{"body":" is\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":" to\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"tail(b)"},{"body":".  Using this idea,\n\timplement ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":" as a\n\tfunction.\n\t","tag":"#text"}],"solution":[{"body":"\n\t  The following function implements general structural equality\n\t  for chapters 1 and 2, assuming that\n\t  ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":" can only be applied\n\t  to two numbers or two strings, and otherwise report an error.\n\t  The ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":" function below\n\t  will only encounter an error when both\n\t  arguments are functions, because it is not clear in chapters 1\n\t  and 2 what equality on functions would mean.\n          ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":22,"eval":true,"prependLength":3,"program":"chap=2&-D4AGtuvwQFiOJFmGRXmC-CBCKRKDRkZZrmTyNQiE90kStjsKjhXHcyBochFWKwnFyAERkSJOQX6QViiXMcUgQX8ojouhyWXygWCopfPkCjTC0VSVVSuUyiUKpUq03qipGIA","body":"def equal(xs, ys):\n    return ((is_pair(ys) and\n             equal(head(xs), head(ys)) and\n             equal(tail(xs), tail(ys)))\n            if is_pair(xs)\n            else is_none(ys)\n            if is_none(xs)\n            else (is_number(ys) and xs == ys)\n            if is_number(xs)\n            else (is_string(ys) and xs == ys)\n            if is_string(xs)\n            else is_none(ys)\n            if is_none(xs)\n            else\n            # we know now that xs is a function\n            (is_function(ys) and xs == ys)) "},{"body":"\n\t  In chapter 3, we\n\t  extend ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":" such that it\n\t  can be applied to any value and give meaningful results (pointer\n\t  equality). The\n\t  ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"equal"},{"body":" function above will\n\t  still be valid with this extended meaning of\n\t  ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"=="},{"body":", but can be simplified\n\t  as follows:\n          ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":23,"eval":true,"prependLength":3,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgugGYCuAdgMYAuAlgPZEgCmAjgQIYA2IZVIARnSAO4AnCmTJ1a3BAGcyBACbiyOBXnpM2ACgAeUgDQg4UgJQAuLCAshBdWYNoaNFKQH0ADswqCNhoyGZE5c0tgkMYWVg0ACzpmOW1jfWjY72Nff0CQzIswzTIPCJ0jfTyKCJ8jIyCsywpVJzcPL0Kq6vpWKT4dEABeboNjHFdhIjINHIjWVidRgCIySKcZ-RnF5eYlkBmpogBrOjkNremZopaLSemNOYWpQ9XN9eXtvYOn44qjIA","body":"def equal(xs, ys):\n    return ((is_pair(ys) and\n             equal(head(xs), head(ys)) and\n             equal(tail(xs), tail(ys)))\n            if is_pair(xs)\n            else xs == ys) "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 2.55","id":"#ex-2.55","child":[{"body":"\n\tThe Python interpreter reads the characters after a double\n        \n\tquotation mark ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"\""},{"body":" until it finds\n\tanother double quotation mark. All characters between the two are part\n\tof the string, excluding the double quotation marks themselves. But what\n\tif we want a string to contain double quotation marks? For this\n\tpurpose, Python also allows\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"single","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" quotation marks\n\tto delimit strings, as for example in\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"'say your name aloud'"},{"body":".\n\tWithin singly-quoted strings, we can use double quotation marks, and\n\tvice versa, so\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"'say \"your name\" aloud'"},{"body":" and\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"\"say 'your name' aloud\""},{"body":" are valid\n\tstrings that have different characters at positions 4 and 14, if we\n\tstart counting at 0. Depending on the font in use, two single\n\tquotation marks might not be easily distinguishable from a double\n\tquotation mark. Can you spot which is which and work out the value of\n\tthe following expression?\n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":24,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=2&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniATAOgMzIIwCgsAcBOAlgHYAuAFAOQBElIAvPSNdQJRA","body":"print('\"' == \"\") "}],"solution":[{"body":"\n\t  The given expression checks if a string containing only one double-quote\n\t  character is equal to the empty string. The resulting value is False.\n\t","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-1","count":1,"href":"/sicpjs/2.3.1#footnote-link-1","child":[{"body":"\n        We can consider two strings to be \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"the same","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\" if they\n\tconsist of the same characters in the same order. Such a definition\n        skirts a deep issue that we are not yet ready to address: the meaning\n        of \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"sameness","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\" in a programming language.  We will return\n\tto this in chapter ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3","href":"/sicpjs/3"},{"body":"\n\t(section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.1.3","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.3"},{"body":").","tag":"#text"}]}]